This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with semantic image segmentation, which is a core problem in computer vision. The use of conditional random fields (CRFs) also suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the mention of computational efficiency may indicate that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) and Graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories, as these fields often deal with large amounts of data and require efficient algorithms for processing.
